✅2022. One of my favorite thing I did this year 🖤 @ladygaga #chromaticaball 🙏 Spiritual experience working on this with @nick_knight @showstudio

✅2022 WEB3 Highlights:
* We successfully sold out our first NFT collection in few hours on @folionft * Created the first web3 digital magazine showcasing my fav creatives and humans
* Had my avatar displayed at Art Basal in Miami and the metaverse * Got lots of new people into Web3 and digital art space . Thank you so much all for playing in the sandbox with me It’s been very fun pushing the limits of creativity, art and technology.
Thank you to all the collectors and people believing in creativity, inclusion and diversity - it means the world to me. We are just at the beginning 🌹 💐🤖 Happy Holidays & Happy 2023 everyone, I love you! ❤️
✅ BEST OF 2022. What a year it has been…! I got to work with so many amazing people …so thankful 🙏 love to all my collaborators and friends 💋

✨ Honored to be part of this special project with @voguearabia ✨ Thank you for inviting me to work on these 10 beautiful covers featuring 10 incredible models, each wearing custom outfits designed by 10 Saudi designers. Together, we celebrate creativity and artistry showcased through color Lavender, symbolic representation of mystery and fantastical beauty💜 Fun fact: Did you know lavender can grow in the desert?! 🌿 A huge shoutout to the amazing photographer duo @domenvandevelde for capturing the magic! A young and talented Belgian duo who moved to the US a few years ago. It’s has been a pleasure collaborating with them since their  arrival, witnessing their artistic journey has been very inspiring. This Vogue cover marks a significant milestone in their career, and I feel grateful to have been able to contribute even a little bit to their amazing journey. 💜 Special thanks to the Editor-in-Chief @mrarnaut  for the unwavering support throughout. 🙏🏼 #VogueArabia #SaudiIssue #LavenderMagic

Feeling grateful on my birthday today! ✨Surrounded by so much love and positivity, I am blessed to have amazing people in my life who inspire me to keep pushing boundaries and creating. I want to thank everyone who has encouraged me to be the best version of myself, even when it meant stepping outside of my comfort zone. While I have experienced many amazing things, I know there is still so much more to come. I am excited for more adventures, more love, and more magic in the years ahead. Thank you for all your birthday wishes mean the world to me, and I am grateful for each and every one of you. Here's to a year filled with joy, and endless possibilities! 🎉🎂✨ 
Oh, and by the way, my giant disco ball collection is growing 🪩🪩🪩 and that little white toy is #Onimaru 🤍 #SWAGGA #birthdayboy #gemini ♊️

✨Birthday blessings from the desert! 🌵🎂✨amazing time on my road trip to Joshua Tree - the perfect place to unwind and connect with nature. theres something magical about being surrounded by these crazy rocks in the desert. 🙏 Thank you for all the birthday wishes and love ❤️ I'm excited for another year of adventure!! ✨

Who’s the Designer - BAD BUNNY Edition 👽 
let me introduce you to the genius designers /artists behind @badbunnypr @rollingstone magazine cover

🖤 @apt.1007 by Spencer Daly: Embracing experimental furniture design, Daly creates a raw, DIY aesthetic using industrial materials like steel, metal, chains, and screws.  He now ventures into body art, accessories and jewerly. #APT1007

💎 @xtended_identity : Blending the boundaries of fashion and digital, this experimental fashion design lab is revolutionizing the concept of jewelry. Their PHYGITAL collection is redefining the future of fashion, pushing the boundaries of what a collection can by merging digital and physical. #xtendedidentity 

🔥 @ottolinger1000 : Berlin-based label created by Christa Bösch and Cosima Gadient. Their counterculture aesthetic and asymmetric silhouettes have captivated a cult following. #ottolinger 

I'm always on the lookout for great talents.  please feel free to DM me, message me, or tag me! Let's connect and celebrate creativity together. ⭐️

Introducing the incredible virtuoso pianist Micah @pianomicah 🎹 We’ve been collaborating together over the past few months and it’s been wonderful to see how he has blossomed into a fabulous artist. As a fellow pianist I can say that Micah's talent is on another level! The new single "MOONS" marks his debut as a vocalist and pop composer. It is an incredibly personal track about Micah’s journey of self-discovery and the freedom to love ❤️ 

Link in bio for “MOONS” video directed by @lukeabby 🖤 photos by @domenvandevelde

✨ Flashing back to my @dazed era—my first cover as Creative Director in 2007, where I made the entire magazine black and white, analogue, and anti-tech. 😎📸 Featuring @luke__worrall by @marianovivanco London in the early 2000s: a creative haven where music, fashion, style, and art collided ✨

Everything used to be so much more spontaneous! ✨ This story was pure magic. It was just a few of us (myself, photographer, model, and makeup artist) We traveled to Lanzerote in Spain and got inspired by the landscape that we decided to pay homage to David Bowie's 'Man Who Fell to Earth.' What made it even more special was that the makeup artist's bag was missing, and he only had glitter in hand. Instead of us freaking out, we went, 'Sure, why not?' And decided to cover the model entirely in glitter. Sometimes the most magical moments happen when you just go with the flow and let the universe do its thing 🖖🏼👽 

ANOTHER MAN MAGAZINE 2006
PHOTO: JEAN-FRANCOIS LEPAGE
